<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[264,1322,463,689]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
COMMENTS. The description of this species was published as this manuscript was about to be submitted. Three puparia from the CFR, initially identified as members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[264,407,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Dialeurodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,407,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Dialeurodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, were found to belong to 
<taxonomicName box="[785,919,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Peracchius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durantae">
<emphasis box="[785,919,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">P. durantae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but no host data are available. As described by Lima &amp; Racca­Filho, the 
<collectingCountry box="[723,798,623,649]" name="Belize" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Belize</collectingCountry>
puparia were also found feeding contiguous with major leaf veins.
</paragraph>
